				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Not true if you communicate with your email provider with SSL/STARTLS/some other encrypted means.  Your emails, if unencrypted with pgp/gpg, will be accessible by your provider, but NOT your ISP (or any other man in the middle for that matter, unless they&#8217;re using SSLSNiff, Dsniff, or some other tool to intercept the key exchange).</p>
