									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>You can frustrate google&#8217;s automated analysis of your email by using a custom address for each person you correspond with.  For example, my mom thinks my email address is:</p>
<p><a href="mailto:mom2JohnDoe@example.com">mom2JohnDoe@example.com</a></p>
<p>It would be possible for google to cross-reference all addresses at a domain, but they are unlikely to because determining what is a single-user private domain and what is a multi-user domain takes a human to get right.</p>
