				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Mako, don&#8217;t take this personal, but I blame you programmer types. &#8220;sheeple&#8221; out there use Gmail because you programmers haven&#8217;t come up with something better. It is possible to create mail, social networks, instant messaging, VOIP apps, that all communicate peer to peer without a central hub. The coming IPv6 switch-over will make this more feasible than ever.</p>
<p>If you build it, WE, the Alpha nerds of our friends and communities will make sure our flocks will use it.</p>
<p><strong><br />
So stop telling us what we already know, and DO something about it already!  :)<br />
</strong></p>
