				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I personally recommend openmailbox for regular mail, they run on free software exclusively. Hosting a personal mailserver is also an alternative, virtual servers are really cheap nowadays if your ISP doesn&#8217;t allow mail servers. However, we should really try to adopt Bitmessage or some other, more secure way of communication.</p>
