								June 8, 2014 at 17:47							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>If you want to host a server on a reliable Internet connection (i.e., at an ISP and not at your home), it will cost hundreds. Well, $200/year is under $17/month. That&#8217;s about the price of a reasonably slow virtual server. I had to upgrade to a more expensive virtual server in order to spam check all of the email I receive.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

