				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Aaron Swartz on RimuHosting.<br />
It&#8217;s an article from 2009, but I thought you should read it.</p>
<blockquote cite="Despite already having sold me a VPS and put a CPU cap on my usage of it, they manually edited my partition to add their SSH key to my authorized_keys, used that to gain root on my box, noticed that a CGI script was using up CPU, and responded by turning off Apache. They didn’t even try to call me to talk about it in advance. They didn’t even call me at all."><p>
<a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/rimuhosting" title="Link to complete article" rel="nofollow"></a></p></blockquote>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

